 of NZ to sustainable transportation (\'Your Future is Electric\'), and publishes the EZoomers e-bike newsletter for NZ (over 600 subscribers). He also displays at the major events related to energy efficiency around New Zealand.\r\n\r\nJace, originally from the US, has been a resident of New Zealand for several years now and is very proud to be contributing to his adopted country. He owned a sports training company in Hawaii teaching windsurfing and beach volleyball for many years and has been hired to train beach volleyball players in the Nelson region as well. Jace is active in social concerns and sports, including mountain biking, beach volleyball, and croquet. He acquired the importation rights for eZee Kinetic electric bikes some years ago and has never looked back. The business has grown with his full time efforts into its development and Jace has been a much published author on the electric bike subject in New Zealand. He continues with expansion of the e-bike offerings and service system put in place years ago, and sees great opportunity and public benefit in his work.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_50\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-50\" alt=\"At work in the Electric Bike Hub Service Center\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/ebh/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/jace-electric-bike-shop-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /> At work in the Electric Bike Hub Service Center[/caption]\r\nWai Won Ching, president of eZee Kinetic electric bikes has been an inventor and originator of so much of what we know about electric bikes today. Originally from Singapore, his e-bikes have been award and race winners on several occasions and continues to be a world leader in the technology. He has also been a frequent visitor to NZ and invited speaker here about e-bike and e-car issues. He is an ardent advocate of zero-emission transportation. He has personally ridden his e-bikes across Africa, Australia, the Silk Road, and other amazing feats to show their utility, just finishing his 6800 kilometer Australia tour in 2013. Wai Won is an amazing CEO in that he is personally involved with the product development and testing of his e-bikes, even though he runs a very large manufacturing operation. His eZee factory ships to 13 countries and has made a great name for itself in value and performance.\r\nHe continues in new product development when others would have retired.\r\n\r\n<strong>Jace Hobbs and the Team</strong>','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2014-04-13 20:15:44','2014-04-13 20:15:44','',0,'http://localhost:8888/ebh2/?page_id=18',0,'page','',0),(19,1,'2014-03-30 01:42:45','2014-03-30 01:42:45','about','About','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision-v1','','','2014-03-30 01:42:45','2014-03-30 01:42:45','',18,'http://localhost:8888/ebh2/18-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2014-03-30 01:42:55','2014-03-30 01:42:55','Electric Bike Hub\r\n\r\n03 545 1122\r\n\r\n021 0511666\r\n\r\njace@electricbikehub.co.nz','Contact','','publish','open','open','','contact','','','2014-04-17 20:14:38','2014-04-17 20:14:38','',0,'http://localhost:8888/ebh2/?page_id=20',0,'page','',0),(21,1,'2014-03-30 01:42:55','2014-03-30 01:42:55','contact','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-v1','','','2014-03-30 01:42:55','2014-03-30 01:42:55','',20,'http://localhost:8888/ebh2/20-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(22,1,'2014-03-30 01:43:27','2014-03-30 01:43:27',' ','','','publish','open','open','','22','','','2014-04-13 19:55:31','2014-04-13 19:55:31','',0,'http://localhost:8888/ebh2/?p=22',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(23,1,'2014-03-30 01:43:27','2014-03-30 01:43:27',' ','','','publish','open','open','','23','','','2014-04-13 19:55:31','2014-04-13 19:55:31','',0,'http://localhost:8888/ebh2/?p=23',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(24,1,'2014-03-30 01:43:27','2014-03-30 01:43:27',' ','','','publish','open','open','','24','','','2014-04-13 19:55:31','2014-04-13 19:55:31','',0,'http://localhost:8888