bility and cost. Unlike other brands of batteries, eZee Kinetic batteries are rated at the actual work they do for you, and not their theoretical capacity. The theoretical rating on the cells is significantly higher than the eZee rating, because practically, batteries will perform less work than the total capacity of the cells. We rate the work they will do. The lithium cells are made in the highest quality manufacturing facility ( Sony Hi-capacity cells at present) and do not suffer the quality control problems that cheap battery companies suffer with. This means that we can realistically offer a guarantee with the battery. So when you look at the pricing for our batteries, and our complete bikes, look at the rated amp hour figure with confidence and know that we stand behind the battery performance. We also recycle our batteries, and these are particularly non-toxic, so it is a real environmental benefit when you ride an EBH product.\r\n\r\nThese batteries charge to  41 volts, so there is reserve voltage to allow for voltage drop on hills.','28 amp hour (1008 watt hours) eZee lithium battery','','publish','open','closed','','28-amp-hour-1008-watt-hours-ezee-lithium-battery','','','2014-04-17 03:32:23','2014-04-17 03:32:23','',0,'http://www.electricbikehub.co.nz/ebh/?post_type=product&#038;p=123',0,'product','',0),(124,2,'2014-04-15 04:37:20','2014-04-15 04:37:20','The 1000 Lumens eZee L1K aspherical lens construction directs light\r\nsemi-spherically downwards, making broad beams and reducing\r\nglare unto incoming traffic. High quality reflectors in the construction\r\ndirects over 90% of the light forward. The high vision, high visibility\r\ngreatly improves the safety and performance of your night ride.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe L1000 is a 1000 lumen front light that runs off a 36V e-bike battery. 1000 lumen means really, really bright. Our standard <a href=\"http://glowwormbicycles.com.au/store/spare-parts/spares-ezee-electric-bicycles/spare-parts-ezee-cadence/front-light-36v-spanninga-e\">36V Spanninga e-bike light</a> is 40 lumen and is already better than what you get on most e-bikes out there. A similar <a href=\"http://glowwormbicycles.com.au/store/accessories/lights/titan-gemini-900-lumen-super-bright-headlight\">super bright bicycle light</a> costs around $200 and would require you to charge its battery every week and take the thing on and off all the time in case of theft. With an e-bike battery on board you don\'t have either of those problems.\r\n\r\nYou can read a users review of the L1000 <a href=\"http://www.pedelecs.co.uk/forum/blogs/aldby/13-ezee-l700-headlight-blinding.html\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nThe L1000 comes standard on some of our premium e-bikes such as the <a href=\"http://glowwormbicycles.com.au/store/ezeebike-electric-bicycles/ezee-torq-alfine\">eZee Torq Alfine   </a> and  Torq NuVinci. It is compatible with other electric bicycles that use 36V batteries.\r\n\r\nThis light mounts to the hole that is present in the top of the most front forks and has a rigid metal mount for toughness and to make sure that the light doesn\'t wander around and blind oncoming cyclists. It has two modes, bright and brighter that you easily switch between with the button on top. Hold the button to turn the light off. There is no flashing mode. If you are intending to plug this into your electric bicycle you may have to connect it straight to the battery output or where the battery powers the controllor. This is because existing light outputs from e-bike controllors may not be expecting such a high power light to connect to them. On good e-bikes this will mean the controllor turns the light or the whole bike off for safety. On cheap e-bikes this may mean the thin lighting wire melts and shorts, burning a fuse in the battery or destroying the controllor. If you are buying this for your eZeebike check with us first and supply your serial number. If you bought your eZeebike a long time ago this light may have to be plugged straight into the controllor. If your eZeebike is more recent it can go straight on.\r\n\r\nThe way to run an L1000 on an older eZee bike is to hook into the main power between the battery and the controllor. The most practical way of achieving this is to connect the L1000 via a long wire, into the auxiliary battery socket which is located under the rear pannier rack. It\'s covered by black heat shrink and is possibly not something you\'ve ever noticed being there. it\'s intended purpose is to allow you to plug more than one battery into an eZeebike at a time for longer rides. If you want to order this light with a long cable and correct Anderson plug on the end, let us know. It can also be made as an Anderson \'piggy back\' or \'inline\' plug so that you can still use the auxiliary battery function.\r\n\r\n</div>','L1000 blaster 36 volt compatible bike light','','publish','open','closed','','l1000-blaster-36-volt-compatible-bike-light','','','2014-04-17 04:04:49','2014-04-17 04:04:49','',0,'http://www.electricbikehub.co.nz/ebh/?post_type=product&#038;p=124',0,'product','',0),(125,2,'2014-04-15 07:05:32','2014-04-15 07:05:32','This is our 26\" 300 average watt motor/controller/kit that will pull over 700 watts on a hill climb.\r\n\r\nCheck the world forums for the thousands of conversions with eZee kits that have resulted in highly satisfied customers. Almost every country has been criss-crossed with eZee electric assist kits. The kits are adaptable to dozens of different configurations and our selection of rack mount or bottle mount batteries has you covered for augmented power. The eZee 26\" wheel is perhaps the most traveled e-bike wheel  in the world. Thousands are traversing landscapes for a decade or more. The kit comes with the grunty  eZee 300 watt hi-torque hub motor, 13 g. cargo bike spokes radiating out to the German Weinman double wall alloy rims, and is finished with a Schwalbe puncture resistant Marathon-Plus tyre. Full parts are supplied to make the pedal ass